titleInfo.title: (SS) Ruelas v. Commissioner of Social Security
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER signed by Magistrate Judge Kendall J. Newman on 12/28/2012 ORDERING 2 Motion to Proceed IFP is GRANTED; Clerk is directed to serve undersigned's scheduling order in Social Security cases; Clerk is further directed to serve a copy of this order on USM; within 14 days from the date of this order, plaintiff shall submit to USM an original and 5 copies of the completed summons, 5 copies of the complaint and 5 copies of the scheduling order and a completed USM-285 form, and shall file a statement with the court that such documents have been submitted to the USM for service of process without prepayment of costs; USM shall serve process not later than 60 days from the date of this order; plaintiff is advised that failure to comply with this order may be grounds for imposition of sanctions. (cc: USM). (Waggoner, D)

titleInfo.title: (SS) Ruelas v. Commissioner of Social Security
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER signed by Magistrate Judge Kendall J. Newman on 8/13/13 ORDERING that within 14 days of this order, the parties shall file a stipulation of dismissal of the action. In the alternative, the Commissioner may file an opposition to plaintiff's motion to dismiss the action within 14 days of this order. Failure to comply with the above deadlines may result in the imposition of monetary or other appropriate sanctions. (Kastilahn, A)
